whereas.text:
Whereas the mental health and well-being of people in the
			 United States is a critical issue that affects not only quality of life, but
			 also the health of communities, families, and economic stability;

Whereas post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) afflicts 15
			 to 20 percent of veterans of the war in Afghanistan and 20 percent of Iraqi war
			 veterans;

Whereas in 2012, over 38,000 people died by suicide in the
			 United States, and more than 500,000 people in the United States attempt
			 suicide each year;

Whereas lack of awareness of one’s mental illness affects
			 approximately 50 percent of individuals with schizophrenia and 40 percent of
			 individuals with bipolar disorder;

paragraph.text:
supports the designation of Mental Health
			 Month in order to place emphasis on scientific facts and findings regarding
			 mental health and to remove the stigma associated with mental illness;

recognizes that
			 mental well-being is equally as important as physical well-being for citizens,
			 communities, businesses, and the economy in the United States;
